<HEADLINE>
FT  13 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Sturge disposal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sturge, the Lloyd's underwriting agency, expects to receive an initial
consideration of Pounds 500,000 for the sale of its members' agencies
business to a management buy-out.
The sum will consist of Pounds 100,000 cash and Pounds 400,000 in preference
shares in Falcon Agencies, the company taking over the business of RW Sturge
and Donner, Sturge's two members' agencies.
In addition RW Sturge and Donner will receive a deferred cash consideration
dependant on future results of Falcon, subject to a limit of Pounds 5m .
The deal requires approval by Sturge shareholders and Lloyd's.
</TEXT>
