<HEADLINE>
FT  12 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sao Paulo closed off 2.1 per cent in volatile trade as short and long
investors arm-wrestled ahead of the futures index and options markets
settlements tomorrow and on October 17.
The Bovespa index of the 55 most-active shares ended down 1,061 at 49,260
points. Turnover was a high RDollars 588.4m (Dollars 705.6m) due to a surge
of options deals.
The amount of open interest Bovespa futures index contracts was high prior
to the settlement. Brazilian markets will be closed today.
</TEXT>
