FT  12 OCT 94 / UK Company News: BOC/ Hewlett deal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BOC, the chemicals company, and Hewlett Packard, the US electronics group,
will today announce the establishment of a network of alliances around the
world to sell anaesthetics and the associated monitoring equipment.
The arrangement involves no cash changing hands but is likely to lead to
some job cuts as the two companies 'streamline' their sales and service
organisations.
BOC said that neither it nor HP would forecast the sales revenue that would
flow through the new sales organisations but that they it expected to
increase their 'access to the Dollars 1bn a year global anaesthesia
equipment market'.
Ohmeda, BOC's healthcare business, based in New Jersey, had 1993 revenue of
Dollars 880m. HP's medical products group, in Massachusetts, had sales last
year of Dollars 1.2bn.
