   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Inchcape, the international motors, services and marketing group, has sold
the services area on the M5 motorway at Strensham, Worcestershire, to its
management for about Pounds 12m, writes Andrew Bolger.
Inchcape acquired the site with TKM, the motor dealer it bought for Pounds
383m in 1992.
