<TEXT>
UK health science group seeks energetic executives with sporting expertise.
Good handicap essential.
Amersham International may have scored a hole-in-one through its link-up
yesterday with Sumitomo Chemical of Japan, but it has one problem - no
golfers on the board. 'Someone is going to have to learn,' says chief
executive Bill Castell, whose Japanese counterpart has a handicap of less
than 10.
But he shouldn't have too much of a problem. While the directors are golfing
duffers, the group has won the UK Pharmaceutical Golf Championships for two
years running. 'I'm amazed,' Castell adds. 'I don't know when the staff get
the time.'
