FT  12 OCT 94 / Letters to the Editor: Life under the big spenders
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr RICHARD BACON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, According to Joe Rogaly, 'today's Conservative ministry has trapped
itself on the shores of free-market minimalism' ('Echoes of Tory voices',
October 7). Rogaly seems to have forgotten that nearly half the British
economy - more than 44 per cent - is in the public sector. What would it be
like under a Labour ministry, full of politicians who were actually keen on
spending other people's money?
