FT  12 OCT 94 / BR admits to job cuts at offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Unions expect to be told next week that more than 1,500 white-collar workers
will lose their jobs at British Rail Infrastructure Services over the next
six months as the organisation is split into 20 separate companies prior to
privatisation.
British Rail yesterday admitted there would be job losses but refused to
confirm the figure of 1,500. Unions believe the main victims will be
managerial and administrative staff.
BRIS, which employs 30,000, is subcontracted by Railtrack to maintain track
and signalling work.
