FT  12 OCT 94 / The Conservatives in Bournemouth: Labour poll boost
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The popularity of Tony Blair's Labour party has risen still further
following his conference triumph, giving his party a 17 point lead over the
Tories, according to a poll in today's Guardian.
In the monthly ICM poll 49 per cent said they would support Labour, 32 per
cent Conservative and 15 per cent the Liberal Democrats. October's survey
results match those for Labour in August, shortly after Mr Blair was elected
party leader. In July they registered 44 per cent and 45 per cent in
September.
